          "grammarTip": "'-beku' attached to a verb means 'must / have to': 'hogu' (go) → 'hogbeku' (have to go). Combine with the destination + '-ge': 'Lalbagh-ge hogbeku' = (I) have to go to Lalbagh."
        },
        {
          "type": "dialogue",
          "speaker": "Auto Driver",
          "speakerEmoji": "🧑🏾",
          "kannada": "Saar, ee time traffic jaasti. Swalpa late aagbahudu.",
          "script": "ಸಾರ್, ಈ ಟೈಮ್ ಟ್ರಾಫಿಕ್ ಜಾಸ್ತಿ. ಸ್ವಲ್ಪ ಲೇಟ್ ಆಗ್ಬಹುದು.",
          "pronunciation": "saar, ee time TRAA-phik JAAS-ti. SWAL-pa late AAG-ba-hu-du",
          "english": "Sir, traffic is heavy this time. It might get a bit late."
        },
        {
          "type": "choice",
          "prompt": "Say it's okay, you're not in a hurry",
          "choices": [
            {
              "kannada": "Parvagilla, nange avasara illa.",
              "script": "ಪರವಾಗಿಲ್ಲ, ನಂಗೆ ಅವಸರ ಇಲ್ಲ.",
              "pronunciation": "par-VAA-gil-la, nan-ge a-va-SA-ra IL-la",
              "english": "It's fine, I'm not in a hurry.",
              "correct": true
            },
            {
              "kannada": "Bega bega! Nange tumba avasara!",
              "script": "ಬೇಗ ಬೇಗ! ನಂಗೆ ತುಂಬಾ ಅವಸರ!",
              "pronunciation": "BEH-ga BEH-ga! nan-ge TUM-ba a-va-SA-ra",
              "english": "Fast, fast! I'm in a big hurry!",
              "correct": false,
              "hint": "He can't beat traffic, and rushing him won't help. A calm 'parvagilla' keeps the ride pleasant."
            },
            {
              "kannada": "Haagadre naanu illi iliyutini.",
              "script": "ಹಾಗಾದ್ರೆ ನಾನು ಇಲ್ಲಿ ಇಳಿಯುತ್ತೀನಿ.",
              "pronunciation": "HAA-gaad-re NAA-nu IL-li i-LI-yu-tee-ni",
              "english": "In that case I'll get off here.",
              "correct": false,
              "hint": "No need to abandon the ride over a little traffic! Just reassure him: 'avasara illa'."
            }
          ],
          "correctReaction": {
            "speaker": "Auto Driver",
            "speakerEmoji": "🧑🏾",
            "kannada": "Olleyadu saar. Hogona.",
            "script": "ಒಳ್ಳೆಯದು ಸಾರ್. ಹೋಗೋಣ.",
            "pronunciation": "OL-le-ya-du saar. ho-GO-na",
            "english": "Good sir. Let's go.",
            "correct": true
          },
          "wrongReaction": {
            "speaker": "Auto Driver",
            "speakerEmoji": "🧑🏾",
            "kannada": "Traffic-alli enu maadakke aagalla saar.",
            "script": "ಟ್ರಾಫಿಕ್‌ನಲ್ಲಿ ಏನು ಮಾಡಕ್ಕೆ ಆಗಲ್ಲ ಸಾರ್.",
            "pronunciation": "TRAA-phik-al-li EH-nu MAA-dak-ke AA-gal-la saar",
            "english": "Nothing can be done in traffic, sir.",
            "correct": false
          },
          "vocab": [
            { "kannada": "avasara", "script": "ಅವಸರ", "pronunciation": "a-va-SA-ra", "english": "hurry / urgency" },
            { "kannada": "bega", "script": "ಬೇಗ", "pronunciation": "BEH-ga", "english": "fast / quickly / soon" },
            { "kannada": "late aagbahudu", "script": "ಲೇಟ್ ಆಗ್ಬಹುದು", "pronunciation": "late AAG-ba-hu-du", "english": "it might be late" },
            { "kannada": "hogona", "script": "ಹೋಗೋಣ", "pronunciation": "ho-GO-na", "english": "let's go" }
          ],
          "grammarTip": "'-bahudu' means 'may / might': 'aagu' (happen) → 'aagbahudu' (it may happen). And '-ona' makes a friendly 'let's...': 'hogona' (let's go), 'tinnona' (let's eat)."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "ap-002",
